<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer16136946185901320736">Charles Frazier is an award-winning author of American historical fiction. His literary corpus, to date, is comprised of three New York Times best selling novels: <i>Nightwoods</i> (2011), <i>Thirteen Moons</i> (2006), and <i>Cold Mountain</i> (1997) - winner of the National Book Award for Fiction.<br/><br/><br/><i>Librarian Note: There are multiple authors in the goodreads database with this name. <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/topic/show/44217-master-list-of-author-disambiguation-by-spaces' rel='nofollow noopener'>more info here.</a></i> </span>
  <span id="freeText16136946185901320736" style="display:none">Charles Frazier is an award-winning author of American historical fiction. His literary corpus, to date, is comprised of three New York Times best selling novels: <i>Nightwoods</i> (2011), <i>Thirteen Moons</i> (2006), and <i>Cold Mountain</i> (1997) - winner of the National Book Award for Fiction.<br /><br /><br /><i>Librarian Note: There are multiple authors in the goodreads database with this name. <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/topic/show/44217-master-list-of-author-disambiguation-by-spaces" rel="nofollow noopener">more info here.</a></i> </span>
